node.text:
Kloof House, a short film that explores the idea of indoors and outdoors coexisting. A family home positioned below Lion’s Head, reinforcing the connection to nature and its cycles.
Share this video with someone who needs to see this project!

#architecture_hunter 
Accordingly to @omniviewdesign, “the main ambition behind the design of the Villa, was to create a home that combines a strong sense of centricity with flowing connections to its natural environment.

To achieve this, the model of the ancient Greek home was studied carefully as a departure point. In fact, the massing and master planning of spiral Villa Is very close to the ancient Greek home.

The ancient Greek geometry of the spiral has been used to organize and Reinvent this master plan as a sequence of activities. The flow of the spiral represents a spectrum from private to public and ends in the Centrepoint.

There, The Villa features an abstraction or the ancient Greek "Hestia", which in this case is materialized as a central exterior sitting under the shade of an olive tree.

This way the goal of the ancient Greek house to offer privatized exterior space is realized, but at the same time strong relationships to the peripheral functions are created •
.
.
.
.
.
.

This year, due to the COVID-19 Pandemic, Casacor, an exhibition of architecture, design and decoration that takes place annually in several cities in Brazil and the world, had to be different.

#CasacorJanelas invited several architects and designers to design spaces inside containers, placed in different spots of the city.

In this edition, LG @lgdobrasil proposed Suite Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos to design the “Connected House”, the container located in Praça Cidade de Milão, with landscape designing by Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

In the kitchen, the architects specified the LG Studio Line appliances, in addition to the Smart LG Side by Side Inverter refrigerator. In the living room, they artistically composed the wall with frames and also with: the LG 65 ”4K OLED HDR Smart TV, awarded as the best TV on the market, the mirrored Artcool air conditioning and the Multi Artcool Gallery.

“LG Connected House” also has other sophisticated products of the brand. Check everything else here: lg.com/br/casa-cor

————

Neste ano, por conta da Pandemia do COVID-19, a Casacor, uma mostra de arquitetura, design e decoração que acontece anualmente em várias cidades do Brasil e do mundo, teve que ser diferente. 

A Casacor Janelas propôs convidar diversos arquitetos e designers para projetarem espaços dentro de containers, espalhados em toda a cidade. 

Nesta edição a LG @lgdobrasil chamou a Suíte Arquitetos @suite_arquitetos para desenhar a “Casa Conectada LG”, cujo container fica na Praça Cidade de Milão, com projeto paisagístico de Bia Abreu @biaabreu_paisagismo. 

Na cozinha, os arquitetos especificaram os eletrodomésticos da Linha Studio LG, além da geladeira Smart LG Side by Side Inverter. 
Já na sala de estar, artisticamente entre os quadros compuseram a parede com: a Smart TV LG 65” 4K OLED HDR, eleita a melhor TV do mercado, o ar condicionado Artcool espelhado e o Multi Artcool Gallery. 

A “Casa Conectada LG” ainda conta com demais sofisticados produtos da marca. Confira tudo aqui: lg.com/br/casa-cor

_project: Viter House 
_architecture: @makhno_design 
_visualization: Lesya Ley 
_location: #Kyiv #Ukraine 

“The architecture of the house was inspired by the winds. Those who carefully and persistently carve rocks, dunes, and waves, creating the perfect geometry of amorphousness. Winds are homeless. They blow and breeze, having neither a starting point nor a destination. However, their winnows do not go unnoticed. This time they left behind a home — we named it Viter (‘wind’ in Ukrainian) House”, explain the designers. 

#concretehouse #homedecor #homeinspiration #whitehouse

This must be one of the most incredible projects we’ve ever seen! Swipe left to better understand the house’s design! 

_project: Casa Ochoquebradas 
_architecture: Ryue Nishizawa
_photographer: @estudiopalma 
_location: Los Vilos, #Chile 
 
The Japanese architect Ryue Nishizawa designed this extremely interesting weekend home with a wavy concrete roof facing the Pacific Ocean. “The roof descends to the ground in place and gently divides the space beneath into segments, which determine the form. There are no walls to speak of - it is like a building of ground and roof only in the midst of abundant nature”, explains the architect. 

#concrete #concretehouse #japanesearchitecture #japanesedesign #ocean

#architecture_hunter 
🎥 WATCH NOW the complete renovation process of a gym, designed by @apo.arquitetura. Link on our stories! 

_project: @academiapinheiros 
_architecture: @apo.arquitetura 
_photographer: @carolina.lacaz 
_engineering: @construtoramlv 
_landscape design: @verticalgardendesign 
_soundproof windows & acoustic glass: @atenuasom
_bathroom items & accessories: @docoloficial 
_windows, glass doors and mirrors: @primo_vidros | @cebracevidros + @agcvidrosbrasil 
_bathroom coating: @colormixrevestimentos 
_visual communication design: @tekaveronessi 
 
For over one year, @architecture_hunter documented the renovation project and construction of Academia Pinheiros, located in Sao Paulo, Brazil, aiming to understand and show the world the importance of architects and designers. The gym, originally built in the 1980’s, had never had the assistance of designers to create a strong brand identity before. The architects @camilladalloca and @alemusto, owners of @apo.arquitetura, had a great challenge, because the client asked for a not so drastic intervention, once the gym could not close on week days, and the work could only happen during the weekends. Adapting an industrial style to the space, the architects’ solution were simple, yet very smart, efficient and cause a great aesthetic impact! 🍃🖤

Watch our short documentary now! Link on our stories or bio! 

#gym #fitness #fitnessdesign #green #gymdesign #braziliarchiteture #arquiteturabrasileira #industrialstyle

_lamp: Clam Pendant
_design: Ahm & Lund for @FritzHansen
_where to buy: @And.Light

Based on a seashell from nature, the Danish design duo created this extraordinary pendant lamp, that takes its shape after the mussel, while it also hides its very own kind of pearl in the middle of the shell. Made of opal glass, the lamp gives a soft and welcoming light, through its two shades. By turning the brass screw, the lower shade can be adjusted so that the light can also be adjusted as desired, combined with a diffuser which provides a glare-free light.

Watch our stories to see the duo building the lamp, and follow @and.light for more outstanding lamps!

#light #lighting #lightingdesign #fritzhansen #clampendant

_project: Witta Beach House 
_architecture: @shaunlockyer 
_landscape design: @conlongroup 
_interior design: @honghenwooddesign 
_photographer: @christopherfrederickjones 
_location: Queensland #Australia 

“Witta is a family beach house situated on the Noosa River. The design draws its inspiration from #BrazilianModernism but seeks to ground itself in the local context, climate and culture. The occupation of the site is heavily defined by the landscape and water, both natural and curated. The outcome of the house represents the culmination of two decades of design philosophy with the privilege and opportunity to execute it to its full potential. A carefully considered and restrained palette of concrete, stone and timber define the clean, robust but warm character of the home. A meticulously executed landscape design and interior fit out complete the environment in which this family will create future memories. An incredible team of client, designers, builders, consultants, and craftsman collaborated to execute the house to a new benchmark for the practice” say the architects. 

#australianarchitecture #australiandesign #beachhouse #beach #house #river #home
